<dl id="n06150e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06150e">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06150e"> 150(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Supposed to have / originated with</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Church Catechism is <mark>supposed to have been written by</mark> Dean Nowell, and was revised and sanctioned by Cranmer. It was intended to be a summary of the cardinal points of faith and duty, &ldquo;to be understood by a child before he comes to be confirmed.&rdquo; <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 6-7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
